nwSysServerName.name: nwSysServerName
nwSysServerName.description: The physical name of this NetWare server.

nwSysSerialNumber.name: nwSysSerialNumber
nwSysSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the instance of the NetWare Operating System running on this server.

nwSysInternalNetNum.name: nwSysInternalNetNum
nwSysInternalNetNum.description: The internal IPX network number of this server.

nwSysServerUpTime.name: nwSysServerUpTime
nwSysServerUpTime.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since this server was last restarted.

nwSysOSSFTLevel.name: nwSysOSSFTLevel
nwSysOSSFTLevel.description: The System Fault Tolerance Level of the NetWare Operating System running on this server.

nwSysOSMajorVer.name: nwSysOSMajorVer
nwSysOSMajorVer.description: The major version number of the NetWare Operating System running on this server.

nwSysOSMinorVer.name: nwSysOSMinorVer
nwSysOSMinorVer.description: The minor version number of the NetWare Operating System running on this server.

nwSysOSReleaseDate.name: nwSysOSReleaseDate
nwSysOSReleaseDate.description: The release date of the NetWare Operating System running on this server.

nwSysOSDescription.name: nwSysOSDescription
nwSysOSDescription.description: A textual description of the NetWare Operating System running on this server.

nwSysOSCopyright.name: nwSysOSCopyright
nwSysOSCopyright.description: The copyright string for the NetWare Operating System running on this server.

nwSysTime.name: nwSysTime
nwSysTime.description: The date and time kept by this server.

nwSysTimeZone.name: nwSysTimeZone
nwSysTimeZone.description: The time zone in which this server resides. The string is in the same format as in the NetWare 'SET TIMEZONE' command.

nwSysLoginState.name: nwSysLoginState
nwSysLoginState.description: The current login state of this Server.

nwSysLanguageID.name: nwSysLanguageID
nwSysLanguageID.description: The national language in use on this server.

nwSysNMASerialNumber.name: nwSysNMASerialNumber
nwSysNMASerialNumber.description: The serial number of the instance of the NetWare Management Agent running on this server. Or, a zero-length string if not applicable.

nwSysNMACopiesAllowed.name: nwSysNMACopiesAllowed
nwSysNMACopiesAllowed.description: The maximum number of instances of the NMA with this serial number allowed by the license agreement. A value of 0 implies no limit.

nwSysDirectoryTree.name: nwSysDirectoryTree
nwSysDirectoryTree.description: The name of the NetWare directory services tree containing this server. Or, a zero-length string if not applicable.

nwSysBinderyContext.name: nwSysBinderyContext
nwSysBinderyContext.description: The container object(s) where the bindery services context(s) is set. Or, a zero-length string if not applicable.

nwSysServerDSName.name: nwSysServerDSName
nwSysServerDSName.description: The Directory Services full distinguished name of this NetWare server, or the zero-length string if not applicable.

nwSysDaylightSavingsStart.name: nwSysDaylightSavingsStart
nwSysDaylightSavingsStart.description: Start of daylight savings time. A language independent representation of the local date and time when the switch to Daylight Savings Time occurs on the server.

nwSysDaylightSavingsEnd.name: nwSysDaylightSavingsEnd
nwSysDaylightSavingsEnd.description: End of daylight savings time. A language independent representation of the local date and time when the switch from Daylight Savings Time occurs on the server.

nwSysDaylightSavingsOffset.name: nwSysDaylightSavingsOffset
nwSysDaylightSavingsOffset.description: The offset applied in time calculations when daylight savings is in effect. This is a signed quantity, and the units are seconds.

nwSysDaylightSavingsStatus.name: nwSysDaylightSavingsStatus
nwSysDaylightSavingsStatus.description: Indicates whether daylight savings time is applicable or not.

nwFSReads.name: nwFSReads
nwFSReads.description: The total number of file reads the file system has made since this server was started. This value provides a relative measure of server activity.

nwFSWrites.name: nwFSWrites
nwFSWrites.description: The total number of file writes the file system has made since this server was started. This value provides a relative measure of server activity.

nwFSReadKBytes.name: nwFSReadKBytes
nwFSReadKBytes.description: The total number of KBytes read by the file system. This value provides a measure of server activity.

nwFSWrittenKBytes.name: nwFSWrittenKBytes
nwFSWrittenKBytes.description: The total number of KBytes written by the file system. This value provides a measure of server activity.

nwFSCacheChecks.name: nwFSCacheChecks
nwFSCacheChecks.description: The total number of checks that have been made against the file cache.

nwFSCacheHits.name: nwFSCacheHits
nwFSCacheHits.description: The total number of times a file cache check has resulted in a hit.

nwFSOpenFiles.name: nwFSOpenFiles
nwFSOpenFiles.description: The number of open files in the file system.

nwFSMaxOpenFiles.name: nwFSMaxOpenFiles
nwFSMaxOpenFiles.description: The maximum number of open files allowed in the file system.

nwFSRecordLocks.name: nwFSRecordLocks
nwFSRecordLocks.description: The current number of record locks.

nwFSMaxRecordLocks.name: nwFSMaxRecordLocks
nwFSMaxRecordLocks.description: The maximum number of record locks allowed.

nwFSMaxSubdirectoryTreeDepth.name: nwFSMaxSubdirectoryTreeDepth
nwFSMaxSubdirectoryTreeDepth.description: The number of levels of subdirectories the OS supports.

nwFSMaxPercentOfVolumeUsedByDir.name: nwFSMaxPercentOfVolumeUsedByDir
nwFSMaxPercentOfVolumeUsedByDir.description: The percentage of a volume that may be used as directory space.

nwFSVolCount.name: nwFSVolCount
nwFSVolCount.description: The number of volumes listed in the volume table

nwFSVolTable.name: nwFSVolTable
nwFSVolTable.description: The volume table lists all the NetWare volumes, whether mounted or not ( see nwVolMounted for more details).

nwFSVolEntry.name: nwFSVolEntry
nwFSVolEntry.description: An entry in the volume table describing a single NetWare Volume

nwVolID.name: nwVolID
nwVolID.description: A unique value for each NetWare volume on the server. The value for each volume must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the agent to the next re- initialization.

nwVolPhysicalName.name: nwVolPhysicalName
nwVolPhysicalName.description: The name of the physical volume (as opposed to any Directory Services (DS) name.

nwVolSize.name: nwVolSize
nwVolSize.description: The size of the volume in KBytes.

nwVolFree.name: nwVolFree
nwVolFree.description: The free space on the volume in KBytes. As this number approaches zero, the volume is running out of space for new or expanding files.

nwVolFreeable.name: nwVolFreeable
nwVolFreeable.description: The amount of freeable space (in KBytes) being used by previously deleted files on this volume. The freeable space can be reclaimed as free space by purging deleted files.

nwVolNonFreeable.name: nwVolNonFreeable
nwVolNonFreeable.description: The non-freeable space (in KBytes) on the volume. This is the space being used by deleted files that cannot be purged. Non-freeable space can be reclaimed as free space when the deleted files become eligible to be purged.

nwVolBlockSize.name: nwVolBlockSize
nwVolBlockSize.description: The block size on the volume in bytes.

nwVolMounted.name: nwVolMounted
nwVolMounted.description: The mount state of the volume. Note that if the volume is not mounted, all the other values in the table, except nwVolName, are invalid. Writing a value of mounted(1) to this object will cause the volume to be mounted if it is currently dismounted. Writing a value of dismounted(2) to this object will cause the volume to be dismounted if the volume is currently mounted.

nwVolAttributes.name: nwVolAttributes
nwVolAttributes.description: A value that represents the attributes of the volume. The value is a sum. This value initially takes the value zero, then for each attribute that is enabled on the volume, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: Attribute Power Block Suballocation 0 File Compression 1 Data Migration 2 Auditing 3 Read Only 4 For example, a read-only volume with suballocation enabled would have a value of 17 (2**4 + 2**0).

nwVolNameSpaces.name: nwVolNameSpaces
nwVolNameSpaces.description: A value representing all the name spaces supported by this volume. The value is a sum. This value initially takes the value zero, then for each name space that is supported by the volume, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: Name Space Power DOS 0 MAC 1 NFS 2 FTAM 3 OS/2 4 NT 5 For example, a volume supporting both the DOS and MAC name spaces would have a value of 3 (2**0 + 2**1).

nwVolTotalDirEntries.name: nwVolTotalDirEntries
nwVolTotalDirEntries.description: The total number of directory table entries available on this volume.

nwVolUsedDirEntries.name: nwVolUsedDirEntries
nwVolUsedDirEntries.description: The number of directory table entries that are currently being used on this volume.

nwVolSegmentCount.name: nwVolSegmentCount
nwVolSegmentCount.description: The number of segments comprising this volume.

nwVolDSName.name: nwVolDSName
nwVolDSName.description: The full Directory Services distinguished name for the volume, or the zero-length string if not applicable.

nwVolFileSystemID.name: nwVolFileSystemID
nwVolFileSystemID.description: The type of the file system on the volume.

nwVolFileSystemName.name: nwVolFileSystemName
nwVolFileSystemName.description: If remote, the remote mount point; e.g. va:/usr/x If local, the zero length string.

nwFSOpenFileTable.name: nwFSOpenFileTable
nwFSOpenFileTable.description: A table of all open files on the server. If a file is opened by more than one connection, multiple entries for the same file will appear in the table.

nwFSOpenFileEntry.name: nwFSOpenFileEntry
nwFSOpenFileEntry.description: An entry in the Open File table providing information about a single open file.

nwOfileVolID.name: nwOfileVolID
nwOfileVolID.description: A number that uniquely identifies a NetWare volume. The value of this object for a particular volume has the same value as the nwVolID object for the same volume.

nwOfileDirectoryNumber.name: nwOfileDirectoryNumber
nwOfileDirectoryNumber.description: A number that uniquely identifies an open file within a NetWare volume.

nwOfileConnection.name: nwOfileConnection
nwOfileConnection.description: The number of the connection that opened the file.

nwOfileVolumeName.name: nwOfileVolumeName
nwOfileVolumeName.description: The physical name of the NetWare volume containing the open file.

nwOfileName.name: nwOfileName
nwOfileName.description: The name of the open file including the directory path.

nwOfileLoginName.name: nwOfileLoginName
nwOfileLoginName.description: The name of the user (if any) who opened the file. If the file was opened by the system or by an NLM, etc., nwOfileLoginName will be the zero-length string.

nwUserCount.name: nwUserCount
nwUserCount.description: The number of entries in the User Account Table.

nwLoginCount.name: nwLoginCount
nwLoginCount.description: The number of licensed connections (logins) in this file server.

nwMaxLogins.name: nwMaxLogins
nwMaxLogins.description: The maximum number of licensed connections (logins) supported by this file server. Zero if unlimited.

nwConnectionCount.name: nwConnectionCount
nwConnectionCount.description: The number of entries in the Connection Table. The current number of connections to this file server(including connection 0 (zero), the system connection).

nwPeakRemoteConnections.name: nwPeakRemoteConnections
nwPeakRemoteConnections.description: The peak number of remote stations that have simultaneously connected to this server. Note that this number does not include connections made by the server itself, nor NLMs running on the server.

nwMaxConnections.name: nwMaxConnections
nwMaxConnections.description: The maximum number of connections supported by this file server. Zero if unlimited.

nwNLMConnections.name: nwNLMConnections
nwNLMConnections.description: The current number of logged in connections used by the system.

nwConnectionTable.name: nwConnectionTable
nwConnectionTable.description: The Connection Table lists all connections used; including those by Workstations, NLMs, and Attachments. Connection 0 (zero) is used by the system.

nwConnectionEntry.name: nwConnectionEntry
nwConnectionEntry.description: An entry in the connections table provides information about a single connection

nwConnectionNumber.name: nwConnectionNumber
nwConnectionNumber.description: The connection number. Connection 0 (zero) is used by the system.

nwConnectionLoginName.name: nwConnectionLoginName
nwConnectionLoginName.description: The login name (Directory Services full distinguished name where appropriate). Zero-length string if not applicable.

nwConnectionTransportDomain.name: nwConnectionTransportDomain
nwConnectionTransportDomain.description: The transport domain of the connection.

nwConnectionTransportAddress.name: nwConnectionTransportAddress
nwConnectionTransportAddress.description: The transport address of the connection.

nwConnectionTime.name: nwConnectionTime
nwConnectionTime.description: The date and time the connection was established.

nwConnectionReadKBytes.name: nwConnectionReadKBytes
nwConnectionReadKBytes.description: The number of KBytes the connection has read since it was established.

nwConnectionWrittenKBytes.name: nwConnectionWrittenKBytes
nwConnectionWrittenKBytes.description: The number of KBytes the connection has written since it was established.

nwConnectionNcpRequests.name: nwConnectionNcpRequests
nwConnectionNcpRequests.description: The number of NCP Requests the connection has made since it was established.

nwConnectionFilesOpen.name: nwConnectionFilesOpen
nwConnectionFilesOpen.description: The number of files that are currently opened by the connection.

nwConnectionRecordsLocked.name: nwConnectionRecordsLocked
nwConnectionRecordsLocked.description: The number of file records that are currently locked by the connection.

nwConnectionPrivilege.name: nwConnectionPrivilege
nwConnectionPrivilege.description: A value that represents the connection's login privileges. The value is a sum. This value initially takes the value zero, then for each privilege that the connection has, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: Privilege Power Supervisor 0 Operator 1 Auditor 2 High_Privilege 3 Second_Authentication 4 Second_High_Privilege 5 For example, a user with both Supervisor and Auditor privileges would have a value of 5 (2**0 + 2**2)

nwConnectionStatus.name: nwConnectionStatus
nwConnectionStatus.description: A value that represents the login status of the user. The value is a sum. This value initially takes the value zero, then for each status that the user has, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: Status Power Not logged in 0 Logged in 1 Need security change 2 MacStation 3 Connection abort 4 Audited 5 Authenticated temporary 6 Audit connection recorded 7 DS audit connection recorded 8 Logout in progress 9 For example a logged in user who needs a security change would have a value of 6 (2**1 + 2**2).

nwQueueCount.name: nwQueueCount
nwQueueCount.description: The number of active queues on this server.

nwQueueTable.name: nwQueueTable
nwQueueTable.description: The Queue table lists all the active NetWare queues including: print, job and archive queues on this server.

nwQueueEntry.name: nwQueueEntry
nwQueueEntry.description: An entry in the Queue table provides information about a single NetWare queue.

nwQID.name: nwQID
nwQID.description: A unique value for each NetWare queue on the server. The value for each queue must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the agent to the next re- initialization.

nwQName.name: nwQName
nwQName.description: The queue name (Directory Services full distinguished name where appropriate). Zero-length string if not applicable.

nwQAddJobState.name: nwQAddJobState
nwQAddJobState.description: This value indicates whether more jobs can be added to this queue. A value of canAddJobs(1) indicates more jobs can be added. A value of cannotAddJobs(2) indicates more jobs cannot be added.

nwQAttachState.name: nwQAttachState
nwQAttachState.description: This value indicates whether queue servers can attach to this queue. A value of canAttach(1) indicates a queue server can attach. A value of cannotAttach(2) indicates a queue server cannot attach.

nwQServiceJobState.name: nwQServiceJobState
nwQServiceJobState.description: This value indicates whether the queue can service jobs. A value of canService(1) indicates that the queue can service jobs. A value of cannotService(2) indicates the queue cannot service jobs.

nwQDirVolName.name: nwQDirVolName
nwQDirVolName.description: The physical name of the volume, where the directory created for this queue resides.

nwQNumJobEntries.name: nwQNumJobEntries
nwQNumJobEntries.description: The number of job entries in the queue.

nwQNumAssignedServers.name: nwQNumAssignedServers
nwQNumAssignedServers.description: The number of servers assigned to the queue.

nwQueueJobTable.name: nwQueueJobTable
nwQueueJobTable.description: The Queue Job table lists all the jobs for all the active queues defined on this server QMS creates a file for each job. The name of that file will be Q$XXXX.NNN where XXXX is the last 4 digits of nwQJobQID and NNN is the job number. Therefore the Q Job File name can be calculated and will not be in the table.

nwQueueJobEntry.name: nwQueueJobEntry
nwQueueJobEntry.description: An entry in the Queue Job table provides information about a particular job in a particular queue.

nwQJobQID.name: nwQJobQID
nwQJobQID.description: A number that uniquely identifies a NetWare queue. The value of this object for a particular queue has the same value as the nwQID object for the same queue.

nwQJobDescription.name: nwQJobDescription
nwQJobDescription.description: The description of the queue job.

nwQJobSize.name: nwQJobSize
nwQJobSize.description: The size of the job file in bytes.

nwQJobControlFlags.name: nwQJobControlFlags
nwQJobControlFlags.description: A value representing the job control flags. The value is a sum. This value initially takes the value zero, then for each job control flag that is set, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: 8h Service Auto-Start 10h Execute 20h Entry Open 40h User Hold 80h Operator Hold

nwQJobUserName.name: nwQJobUserName
nwQJobUserName.description: The name of the user who submitted the job (Directory Services full distinguished name where appropriate). Zero-length string if not applicable.

nwQJobTargetServerName.name: nwQJobTargetServerName
nwQJobTargetServerName.description: The target server name (Directory Services full distinguished name where appropriate).. The zero length string will be returned for 'Any Server'.

nwQJobTargetDateTime.name: nwQJobTargetDateTime
nwQJobTargetDateTime.description: The target date and time. When the job is to be printed. A job may be first in queue but may not print because this is set to some other time.

nwQJobServerName.name: nwQJobServerName
nwQJobServerName.description: The server currently processing the job (Directory Services full distinguished name where appropriate).. If the job is not being handled currently, this field will be a zero-length string.

nwQueueServerTable.name: nwQueueServerTable
nwQueueServerTable.description: The Queue Server Table lists all the assigned servers for all the active NetWare queues on this instrumented server. For each active queue on the server, zero or more entries will exist, one for each server assigned to service that particular queue.

nwQueueServerEntry.name: nwQueueServerEntry
nwQueueServerEntry.description: An entry in the Queue Server table provides information about the assignment of a particular server to a particular queue.

nwQServerQID.name: nwQServerQID
nwQServerQID.description: A number that uniquely identifies a NetWare queue. The value of this object for a particular queue has the same value as the nwQID object for the same queue.

nwQServerID.name: nwQServerID
nwQServerID.description: A unique value for each server servicing this queue. The value for each server must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the agent to the next re- initialization.

nwQServerName.name: nwQServerName
nwQServerName.description: The name of a queue server servicing this queue (Directory Services full distinguished name where appropriate). Zero-length string if not applicable..

nwQServerStatus.name: nwQServerStatus
nwQServerStatus.description: The status of the Queue Server.

nwOdiLslEnqSendCount.name: nwOdiLslEnqSendCount
nwOdiLslEnqSendCount.description: The Link Support Layer's Enqueued Send Count, this is the current number of send packets that have been placed in a send queue.

nwOdiOsPktRcvBuffer.name: nwOdiOsPktRcvBuffer
nwOdiOsPktRcvBuffer.description: The current number of packet receive buffers being used by the operating system.

nwOdiOsMaxPktRcvBuffers.name: nwOdiOsMaxPktRcvBuffers
nwOdiOsMaxPktRcvBuffers.description: The maximum number of packet receive buffers that the operating system can allocate. This object is settable and can also be set through the nwSetParamTable.

nwOdiOsMinPktRcvBuffers.name: nwOdiOsMinPktRcvBuffers
nwOdiOsMinPktRcvBuffers.description: The minimum number of packet receive buffers that the operating system can allocate. This value can only be changed at startup time from STARTUP.NCF; therefore it is settable only through the nwSetParamTable.

nwSft3Engine.name: nwSft3Engine
nwSft3Engine.description: The type of the this engine.

nwSft3EngineState.name: nwSft3EngineState
nwSft3EngineState.description: The state of this engine. Note the msEngine does not know its state and thus will always be unknown(1).

nwSft3EngineTable.name: nwSft3EngineTable
nwSft3EngineTable.description: Information about each engine which comprises an SFT- III server.

nwSft3EngineEntry.name: nwSft3EngineEntry
nwSft3EngineEntry.description: Information about a particular engine in an SFT-III server.

nwSft3EngineInternalNetNum.name: nwSft3EngineInternalNetNum
nwSft3EngineInternalNetNum.description: The internal IPX network number of this server.

nwNCPPacketSignatures.name: nwNCPPacketSignatures
nwNCPPacketSignatures.description: The security level currently in force on this server.

nwNCPPeakUseCount.name: nwNCPPeakUseCount
nwNCPPeakUseCount.description: NCP peak station in use count.

nwNCPForgedPkts.name: nwNCPForgedPkts
nwNCPForgedPkts.description: The count of NCP requests that were forged packets.

nwNCPBeingProcesseds.name: nwNCPBeingProcesseds
nwNCPBeingProcesseds.description: The count of NCP requests that were already being processed.

nwNCPNoAvailConns.name: nwNCPNoAvailConns
nwNCPNoAvailConns.description: The count of NCP requests that were not processed because there were no available connections.

nwNCPInvalidPacketSigs.name: nwNCPInvalidPacketSigs
nwNCPInvalidPacketSigs.description: NCP invalid packet signature error count.

nwWDTimeBeforeFirstPkt.name: nwWDTimeBeforeFirstPkt
nwWDTimeBeforeFirstPkt.description: The time before the first Watchdog Packet in seconds.

nwWDTimeBetweenPkts.name: nwWDTimeBetweenPkts
nwWDTimeBetweenPkts.description: The time between Watchdog Packets in seconds.

nwWDNumPktsToSend.name: nwWDNumPktsToSend
nwWDNumPktsToSend.description: The number of Watchdog Packets to Send.

nwWDCurrentState.name: nwWDCurrentState
nwWDCurrentState.description: The current Watchdog State. Note: this is only available in 4.0, will be unknown in 3.11

nwNLMTable.name: nwNLMTable
nwNLMTable.description: The nwNLMTable augments the hrSWRunTable in the Host Resources MIB to provide additional NetWare specific information.

nwNLMEntry.name: nwNLMEntry
nwNLMEntry.description: An entry in the NLM table provides additional information about a particular NLM.

nwNLMIndex.name: nwNLMIndex
nwNLMIndex.description: A number that uniquely identifies an NLM. The value of this object for a particular NLM has the same value as the hrSWRunIndex object, defined in the HOST- RESOURCES-MIB, for the same NLM.

nwNLMDescription.name: nwNLMDescription
nwNLMDescription.description: A text string that describes this NLM.

nwNLMTotalMemory.name: nwNLMTotalMemory
nwNLMTotalMemory.description: The total memory, in bytes, used by this NLM. This is a composite total of Short Term Memory, Semi-Permanent Memory, and Non-movable Cache Memory allocated by the NLM, plus the sizes of the code and data sections of this instance of an NLM.

nwNLMCopyright.name: nwNLMCopyright
nwNLMCopyright.description: The copyright string for this NLM.

nwNLMProtectionDomain.name: nwNLMProtectionDomain
nwNLMProtectionDomain.description: The protection level at which this NLM is executing.

nwNLMMajorVer.name: nwNLMMajorVer
nwNLMMajorVer.description: The major version number of this NLM.

nwNLMMinorVer.name: nwNLMMinorVer
nwNLMMinorVer.description: The minor version number of this NLM.

nwNLMRevision.name: nwNLMRevision
nwNLMRevision.description: The revision level of this NLM.

nwNLMReleaseDate.name: nwNLMReleaseDate
nwNLMReleaseDate.description: The date and time this NLM was released

nwSetCategoryTable.name: nwSetCategoryTable
nwSetCategoryTable.description: A table of NetWare SET parameter categories

nwSetCategoryIndex.name: nwSetCategoryIndex
nwSetCategoryIndex.description: A unique value for each category of SET commands

nwSetCategoryName.name: nwSetCategoryName
nwSetCategoryName.description: A descriptive name of this category of SET commands

nwSetParamTable.name: nwSetParamTable
nwSetParamTable.description: A table of the NetWare SET parameters. This table emulates the NetWare SET command. Note that some of the parameters can also be set through other MIB objects

nwSetParamEntry.name: nwSetParamEntry
nwSetParamEntry.description: An entry in the SET parameter table provides information about a particular parameter.

nwSetParamCategoryIndex.name: nwSetParamCategoryIndex
nwSetParamCategoryIndex.description: A number that uniquely identifies a Set parameter category. The value of this object for a particular category has the same value as the nwSetCategoryIndex object for the same category.

nwSetParamIndex.name: nwSetParamIndex
nwSetParamIndex.description: An index which uniquely identifies this set parameter within the category

nwSetParamName.name: nwSetParamName
nwSetParamName.description: The name of the settable parameter

nwSetParamType.name: nwSetParamType
nwSetParamType.description: The type of the parameter. All types are integer- valued except 'string', which is string-valued. number: integer boolean: 0 == FALSE, non-zero == TRUE ticks: 1 tick == 3600/65535 == approx 55 millisecs blockShift: integer timeOffset: [+|-]hh:mm:ss converted to seconds string: character string trigger: integer

nwSetParamValueInteger.name: nwSetParamValueInteger
nwSetParamValueInteger.description: The current value of the parameter if integer-valued. Zero otherwise.

nwSetParamValueString.name: nwSetParamValueString
nwSetParamValueString.description: The current value of the parameter if string-valued. The zero-length string otherwise.

nwSetParamLowerLimit.name: nwSetParamLowerLimit
nwSetParamLowerLimit.description: The lower limit of the parameter if integer-valued.

nwSetParamUpperLimit.name: nwSetParamUpperLimit
nwSetParamUpperLimit.description: The upper limit of the parameter if integer-valued. The maximum length of the string if string-valued.

nwSetParamDescrLength.name: nwSetParamDescrLength
nwSetParamDescrLength.description: The total length (in octets) of the parameter description string, which can be retrieved in segments from the nwSetDescrTable.

nwSetParamMode.name: nwSetParamMode
nwSetParamMode.description: A value defining how and when the command takes effect. The value is a sum. This value initially takes the value zero, then for each place the parameter can be set from, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: Set From Power Console 0 AUTOEXEC.NCF 1 STARTUP.NCF 2 For example, a parameter that can be set from either the console or AUTOEXEC would have a value of 3 (2**0 + 2**1). On a read, a bit will be set for each place the parameter can be set from. On a write, bits should be set to specify where the set command should be placed. If nwSetParamValue is written without nwSetParam also being set in the same PDU, the parameter will be set as if at the console; unless it is a parameter which can only be set in STARTUP.NCF in which case an error will be returned

nwSetDescrTable.name: nwSetDescrTable
nwSetDescrTable.description: A table of description string segments for each NetWare SET parameter. This table allows for long description strings to be retrieved in segments. A complete description string can be reconstituted by concatenating the ordered set of string segments. The length of the complete string is available through the nwSetParamTable.

nwSetDescrEntry.name: nwSetDescrEntry
nwSetDescrEntry.description: An entry in the SET description table contains one segment of a NetWare SET parameter description string. The complete description string can be reconstituted by concatenating the ordered set of string segments. The length of the complete string is available through the nwSetParamTable.

nwSetDescrCategoryIndex.name: nwSetDescrCategoryIndex
nwSetDescrCategoryIndex.description: A number that uniquely identifies a Set parameter category. The value of this object for a particular category has the same value as the nwSetCategoryIndex object for the same category.

nwSetDescrParamIndex.name: nwSetDescrParamIndex
nwSetDescrParamIndex.description: A number that uniquely identifies a Set parameter. The value of this object for a particular parameter has the same value as the nwSetParamIndex object for the same parameter.

nwSetDescrIndex.name: nwSetDescrIndex
nwSetDescrIndex.description: An ordinal that indicates this segment's relative position in the complete description string for this NetWare SET Parameter.

nwSetDescription.name: nwSetDescription

nwUserAcctTable.name: nwUserAcctTable
nwUserAcctTable.description: The User Account Table lists all user accounts in this file server. Users in the table may or may not be logged in currently. The information in this table is applicable only to NetWare 3.11 and 3.12 servers, or NetWare 4.10 servers with Bindery Services enabled. In the case of Bindery Services, data is only available for those users in the Bindery context(s) of the server. In a 4.10 server without Bindery Services enabled, this table will be empty

nwUserAcctEntry.name: nwUserAcctEntry
nwUserAcctEntry.description: An entry in the User Account table provides information on a single user account. The information in this table is applicable only to NetWare 3.11 and 3.12 servers, or NetWare 4.10 servers with Bindery Services enabled. In the case of Bindery Services, data is only available for those users in the Bindery context(s) of the server. In a 4.x server without Bindery Services enabled, this table will be empty

nwUserID.name: nwUserID
nwUserID.description: A unique value for each NetWare user with an account on the server. The value for each user must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the agent to the next re-initialization.

nwUserName.name: nwUserName
nwUserName.description: The user's login name (Directory Services full distinguished name where appropriate). Zero-length string if not applicable.

nwUserDiskUsage.name: nwUserDiskUsage
nwUserDiskUsage.description: The amount of disk space, in KBytes, this user is occupying across all volumes on this server.

nwUserLastLoginTime.name: nwUserLastLoginTime
nwUserLastLoginTime.description: The time the user last logged in to this server.

nwUserAccountStatus.name: nwUserAccountStatus
nwUserAccountStatus.description: The status of this user's account

nwUserPasswordStatus.name: nwUserPasswordStatus
nwUserPasswordStatus.description: The status of this user's password.

nwUserBadLoginTransport.name: nwUserBadLoginTransport
nwUserBadLoginTransport.description: The transport domain (protocol) the user used to log in with bad password last time, valid only if the variable nwUserBadLoginAttempt is larger than zero.

nwUserBadLoginAddress.name: nwUserBadLoginAddress
nwUserBadLoginAddress.description: The address the user used to log in with bad password last time, valid only if the variable nwUserBadLoginAttempt is larger than zero.

nwUserBadLoginAttempts.name: nwUserBadLoginAttempts
nwUserBadLoginAttempts.description: The number of times the user attempted to log in with a bad password since the server started. The number would be 0xFFFF if the number of bad login attempts has exceeded the bad login threshold and the account has been locked.

nwUserVolUsageTable.name: nwUserVolUsageTable
nwUserVolUsageTable.description: The User Volume Usage Table lists the amount of volume space used by each user. It is indexed so you can easily find out how much space a particular user is using on each volume.

nwUserVolUsageEntry.name: nwUserVolUsageEntry
nwUserVolUsageEntry.description: An entry in the User Volume Usage table provides information about the amount of space a particular user is using on a particular volume.

nwUserVolUsageUser.name: nwUserVolUsageUser

nwUserVolUsageSpaceUsed.name: nwUserVolUsageSpaceUsed

nwUserVolUsageLimit.name: nwUserVolUsageLimit
nwUserVolUsageLimit.description: The amount of volume space, in KBytes, to which this user is limited. 2147483647 if no limit.

nwVolUsageTable.name: nwVolUsageTable
nwVolUsageTable.description: The Volume Usage Table lists the amount of space on each volume used by each user. It is indexed so that you can easily find all the users who are occupying space on a particular volume.
